leads.lead_text: Juvenile leaves glossy green; Mt Arapiles and northern Grampians only
Juvenile leaves glaucous or blue-green; widespread
Bark light brown, thin, finely fibrous, peppermint-like, sparsely-fractured (smooth in appearance), extending to the upper trunk; Lerderderg State Park
Bark grey to brown, thick, often crusty, tessellated and scaly, box-like, either persisting to the secondary branches or forming a stocking on the lower trunk
Rough bark only as a stocking on lower trunk; bark above loosely-attached, non-fibrous; bark on branches smooth; Brisbane Ranges only
Box-like bark extending to the minor branches; bark on lower trunk thick, crusty and deeply fractured, scaly or tessellated above; widespread
